  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "To make this a speedy recipe, you can cook the sweet potatoes in the microwave. Wash the sweet potatoes and poke them all over with a fork. Wrap the potatoes in wet kitchen paper and place in a microwave-safe bowl or plate. Microwave the sweet potatoes for 10-12 mins, until a knife pierces through very easily. Keep cooking and checking at 5 min intervals."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Meanwhile, make the filling. Tear or cut the mushrooms into bite-sized pieces. Add a little drizzle of olive oil to a large frying pan, then add the mushrooms and a pinch of salt. Cook, stirring occasionally, over a medium heat for about 8 mins."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Drain the chickpeas and add these to the pan, along with the spinach. Add a drizzle of soy sauce if you like and cook for 5 mins until the spinach has wilted and the mushrooms are caramelised."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "To make the soy tahini drizzle, juice the lime into a small bowl. Add the remaining ingredients and whisk together until smooth."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "To serve, slice the sweet potatoes open and mash them down slightly with a fork. Season with salt and pepper before loading with the mushroom chickpea filling. Drizzle over plenty of tahini sauce and top with your chosen toppings."
    }
  ],
